definition:
A woman of the tribe of Ephraim living at the time of Divided Monarchy, only mentioned at 1Ch.7.24; 
 daughter of: Beriah (H1283H); 
 sister of: Rephah (H7506) and Resheph (H7566) 
 § Sherah = "kinswoman"
 daughter of Ephraim and foundress of the Beth-horons and of a town called after her Uzzen-sherah
